The paper discusses a library for robot reachability analysis and base placement, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reachability maps and manipulation tasks suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the library's performance also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
